title: For Sale:  hunting light
postcontent:
$100 or trade for the right item just let me know what you have 
Made for Rifle hunter's, We use high quality LED's that emit the color of light of your choice and our lights don't need replacement bulbs because they will last 100,000 hours of use and if one ever happens to go out we will replace it for free.


Destroyer with White LED - 190 + yards with a average scope.


If you have a scope that does well in low light these distances will be greatly increased and we have customers that have told us with their scopes that do excellent in low light that they can see animals out to 300 yards with our red Destroyer.

Hunting in Rain,Snow and high humidity will lower the max yardage you can see with The Destroyer or any light.

The Destroyer is about 7 inches long and weighs about 9 ounces with battery(s).

Runs on one 18650 rechargeable battery or two CR123A batteries.  

Run time with one 18650 battery- Red LED = 2.5 hours at full power, Green, White and Blue 2+ Hours at full power and then another 2+ hours with the light slowly dimming over that time.

Run time with 2 CR123A batteries will vary depending on brand but you will get about 1 hour of run time at full power on all colors.

Works great in all weather conditions. Hot or very cold temperatures will not effect the light at all but temperatures below 10 degree's will shorten the battery run times a little.

You will be able to mount the Destroyer to virtually any gun

We believe the Destroyer is going to revolutionize the way you hunt, Pigs, coyotes, foxes, bobcats, and all other kinds of predators at night. No more carrying those big bulky spotlights with heavy battery packs and then messing with red lenses to only watch you light output to be cut way down. No more trying  to use lights made for bow hunters that wont reach the distance you want to shoot.

title: For Sale:  Mossberg 715T Modified
postcontent:
Here is a Mossberg 715T .22 Cal. One thing I noticed when I bought this firearm was the plastic shell around it and how would that affect performance . I bought it any way and went to the range with it and after a couple trips and a couple of disassemblies I noticed I had to re-zero it each time . Due to the fact that the shell is plastic and is constantly changeing due to the temp and re placement each time of the scope . To combat this I cut two notches on each side of the shell so I could access the weaver mount that is part of the reciever itself . Once a scope was connected to that , no more issues , no more varibles to get in the way . No matter what goes on with the cover the scope is unaffected . It is now a great little plinker with no issues . Maybe 700 rounds has been down the pipe . 225.00 is for the rifle itself + the 1 mag that came with it  , and for all I am offering the price is 325.00 Or seperate componants listed . I have flip up caps for the scope . You can do the math .
Rifle=225.00
Scope (3 X 9 X 32 IR) 70.00
Bi-Pod= 45.00
2 Extra mags @30.00 ea. =60.00
Case=25.00
The prices listed are minus S&H I paid to get them here . Would rather sell the lot for 325.00 as I am wanting to do an AR build . Prices  are firm . Only trades considered would be a complete AR Lower of equal value , no composites please ,and please be realistic with your offers , I don't have to sell , and if I don't that is OK too . title: For Sale/Trade:  WTT ; ANTIQUE JAPANESE SWORD SHINTO ERA.
postcontent:
I have for trade the following;

Antique Japanese Nihonto Wakazashi sword from the Shinto Era.

Sword details;

This is an unsigned sword with an NTHK attribution to Hisamichi.

Hisamichi was a member of the Mishina School and there were several 
generations using this name. 

It is in reasonable polish there are some scuff marks on it but the details 
of the hamon and hada are clearly visible and all the detail can be seen. 

The fittings are fairly plain and in keeping with what is a quite austere and 
powerful blade  (typically mishina in my experience).

Shinto Era smith's worked from around 1650 to 1800.

I would put this sword to be very early Shinto, probably around 1650 to 1700.

This sword would retail well over 3500.00 if not more, as it is made the traditional way Japanese swords were made, and no Chinese junk here, superb craftsmanship on this blade, and all of the fitting as well.


This sword is papered also, which adds more value to it, it has NTHK papers.

title: For Sale/Trade:  1904 Mauser 8mm German Rifle
postcontent:
This is a 1904 Mauser 8mm German Rifle. I bought it locally at a gun store and as the story goes based on the markings on the rifle it was built in 1904 in Germany. After WWII it was surrendered to the Swiss Army and they stamped it with their crest. 

It was then delivered back to West Germany where the US had setup some of the armories to restock the Mausers with sport stocks and then serialized and sent over to the states for reselling.

The stock is in great condition and the barrel has very little patina on it. It fires great and the only reason I am selling it is because I have a few Mausers and I want to buy a SKS.

title: For Sale:  1975 Marlin 336 30-30 with extras, looks almost new
postcontent: I am selling this very nice Marlin 336 lever action rifle in 30-30 caliber.  The rifle looks almost new and was manufactured in 1975.  The year of manufacture is important because in 1976 Marlin went from a forged steel receiver to a cast steel receiver and the forged is much stronger and operates quite smooth.  This rifle has had so few rounds through it that it will be a very long time before it'll break anything.  At my asking price of $450 I will include a stock pad with 8 rounds of ammo, a full box of Federal ammo and a hard case.  The rifle has a weaver/picatinny type scope mount on the top of the frame but no scope is mounted at this time.  If you use tall see-through rings you can still use the iron sights and you wound need to add a trigger extender to clear a low scope.  Very nice rifle at a very fair price.  Not really looking to trade but will listen to an interesting offer.  Please contact me through the email link and give your contact information and I'll get back to you.  Low-ballers will be ignored.  The rifle is clean and oiled and ready to shoot.
